  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Poor coordination and organisation for blood transfusion&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My dad was referred from Heartlands hospital by his Oncologist a week ago for a blood transfusion to boost his red blood cells. After under going one test last Friday (July 19th) he arrived to his appointment on Monday 22 July at 8am in Solihull expecting to receive the transfusion. He had to wait 4 hours for first the transfusion. He said that he was told that he should have had two blood test, not one. He also said that nobody seemed to know how much blood was contained in a 'bag' - are these not clearly stated like on a drink bottle? Feel that the whole experience of Solihull/Heartland is that departments do not communicate effectively which does not inspire confidence. 

By submitting your review you confirm that the factual statements within it are true and that the opinions expressed are your own honestly held opinions, or those of the person on whose behalf you are commenting. - True.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
